		<IRequirement type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID 112f242b-f4e9-4e40-a4f6-debf060e47e8</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Movement</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">1.2.1990::0:0:0</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_description type="p"><IDescription type="e">
				<_text type="a">Movement%0D
The transitioin to the gate movement in the given direction requires the following steps:%0D
1. Turn on the collision detector%0D
2. Optional activation of the signaling lamp%0D
3. Turning on the gate drive%0D
During the movement taking place in a given direction, the following actions should be repeated every fixed period of time:%0D
1. Send a signal about the last travelled distance to the Controller.%0D
2. Check the occurrence of a collision and if the collision detector signals it, stop the gate movement%0D
3. If the signaling option is active, flash the lamp.</_text>
			</IDescription>
			</_description>
			<_modifiedTime type="a">6.2.2026::10:31:56</_modifiedTime>
			<_body type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1250\deff0\deflang1045{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset238 MS Shell Dlg;}{\f1\fnil\fcharset238{\*\fname Arial;}Arial CE;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs17 Movement\par%0D
\f1\fs20 The transitioin to the gate movement in the given direction requires the following steps:\par%0D
1. Turn on the collision detector\par%0D
2. Optional activation of the signaling lamp\par%0D
3. Turning on the gate drive\par%0D
During the movement taking place in a given direction, the following actions should be repeated every fixed period of time:\par%0D
1. Send a signal about the last travelled distance to the Controller.\par%0D
2. Check the occurrence of a collision and if the collision detector signals it, stop the gate movement\par%0D
3. If the signaling option is active, flash the lamp.\par%0D
}%0D
</_body>
		</IRequirement>
