		<IRequirement type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID a3ef417e-db68-47ee-abf9-b3f7e6b1791b</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Receiving signal from RC</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">1.2.1990::0:0:0</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_modifiedTime type="a">6.2.2026::10:30:46</_modifiedTime>
			<_lastID type="a">2</_lastID>
			<_body type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1250\deff0\deflang1045{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset238{\*\fname Arial;}Arial CE;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 After receiving the signal, the reciever should:\par%0D
1. Validate the recorded signal according to the defined requirements.\par%0D
2. If the signal meets the requirements, send it to the Controller for Interpretation\par%0D
2.1. If the gate was moving at a given moment, it should be stopped, remembering the direction in which it was moving\par%0D
2.2. If the gate was at rest, start the movement in the opposite direction to the previous one\par%0D
3. If the signal is incorrect, ignore it.\par%0D
}%0D
</_body>
			<AggregatesList type="e">
				<value>GUID fbaa6aa9-f1f9-459e-9a4e-2b1f1ca6a32c</value>
